Comments.
There is slight variation in coloration in examined specimens, even within one series of specimens. For example, Bucasia (
Queensland
) specimens are slightly darker overall (
Figs. 47, 48
); in some female specimens, most of the posterior pronotal lobe is also dark like the anterior lobe, and connexiva have intersegmental areas with broad dark bands; and in male specimens the abdominal venter is dark.
